{
  "stem": "4670.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And he suggested that my father should invest in certain things because none of the businesses were really working out.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Unfortunately, we never realized that this man who my father trusted was a gambler.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And the sad thing about that was that he-- my dad had invested much more than we could afford, and the man apparently gambled away, and then he committed suicide.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And here we were in France, with no business, with no livelihood.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "My sister Margot and I had been in school, and I had become pretty fluent in French, but we saw no way that we could make a living there.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We also found there was a resistance against the Germans.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "That's something we hadn't counted on.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Even though we were Jewish, the French had still carried a grudge over us for so many years about the Germans.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And we were many times we were called [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So my dad really felt we couldn't stay there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "As far as the family in the United States, for some reason, my dad never really contacted them at that time.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "He was in touch with his private secretary we-- we were close friends with, from-- originally from the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "She had taken her mother to Holland, and we were in touch with her.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And she felt, with their correspondence, that we should move to Holland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And without hesitation, my dad decided that's what we're gonna do.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "I remember my mother once, just before we left for Holland, she-- excuse me-- went to see my grandparents, went back to Germany, and we were very worried about that.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "She was there I think for about a week, because my grandmother had become ill.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And as soon as my mother returned, we went on to Holland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not at that time.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
